bilingual.source: She finds it easy to communicate with her peer.
bilingual.target: 她发现与她的同龄人沟通很容易。

bilingual.source: He always tries to impress his peer group.
bilingual.target: 他总是试图给他的同龄人群体留下深刻印象。

bilingual.source: The students were encouraged to work with their peer.
bilingual.target: 学生们被鼓励与他们的同龄人合作。

bilingual.source: He feels more comfortable sharing his thoughts with a peer.
bilingual.target: 他觉得与同龄人分享他的想法更舒服。

bilingual.source: The teacher asked the students to review each other's work as peer feedback.
bilingual.target: 老师要求学生们互相审查对方的作业作为同龄人反馈。

bilingual.source: There's no doubt that our peer groups exert enormous influence on our behavior.
bilingual.target: 毫无疑问，同龄人群体对我们的行为产生了巨大的影响。

bilingual.source: Perhaps they have a better peer group.
bilingual.target: 也许他们有更好的同龄人小组。

bilingual.source: The effect of peer pressure cannot be underestimated.
bilingual.target: 同龄人的压力作用不能低估。

bilingual.source: Genes play a significant role, as do peer relationships.
bilingual.target: 基因扮演了一个重要的角色，如同同龄人之间的人际关系那么重要。

bilingual.source: It's not clear why, but one idea is that kids are susceptible to peer influence, and forming peer groups around bullies helps the bad behavior spread.
bilingual.target: 目前尚不清楚其原因，但有一种观点认为，孩子容易受到同龄人的影响，在欺负者周围形成同龄人群体有助于不良行为的传播。

list.abstract: peer（英 [pɪə]，美 [pɪr]），英语单词，作动词时，为凝视；盯着看；费力地看。作名词时，为贵族；同辈；同龄人。短语搭配有peer pressure（同侪压力, 朋辈压力）、peer review（同行评估, 同行审查, 同业审查）。例句为“They do not fund peer-reviewed research.（他们不资助同行评审的研究。）”
一种基于eclipse上的插件程序，全称是peer review eclipse plug-in. eclipse是IBM开发的一种软件开发平台，它是一种支持不同编程语言的开发环境，为多种语言编程环境提供了一个平台。还可以在eclipse上面开发好多插件以增强功能，例如prep就是一种：即基于eclipse上的同行评审插件。可以查看词条eclipse和同行评审以更好的理解peer的作用。

yingyinNormal.en: Ah, here's the alcohol and drug peer pressure Mother warned me about.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这就是我妈警告过我的那种同辈人会教唆我喝酒和嗑药的情景。

yingyinNormal.en: Lord Moran, Peer of the Realm. Minister for Overseas Development. Pillar of the Establishment.
yingyinNormal.zh: 莫兰爵士，上议院成员，海外发展部大臣，上层建筑之一。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, gentlemen, have you reached a decision? I'm in. Me, too. Oh, damn it. Peer pressure. Fine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 先生们，做出决定了么？我加入。我也加入。晕死，给我压力，从了。

yingyinNormal.en: No, no, no, she doesn't want that. She needs a point-to-point peer network with a range extender. Thank you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不，她不需要那个，她需要一个扩大范围的点对点网络。谢谢你。

yingyinNormal.en: Would it be so bad? The only poet peer I am familiar with is Lord Byron. And I presume you all know how that ended.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那很糟糕吗？我唯一熟悉的贵族诗人就是拜伦勋爵。我想你该知道他的下场吧。

yingyinNormal.en: But if you did, you'd open yourself to peer based mocking, such as, hey, Leonard, how was your dinfast with Priya last night?
yingyinNormal.zh: 不过你要是真这么叫的话，你肯定会被别人笑死，人家肯定会说“莱纳德，你昨晚跟普丽娅的早晚餐吃的好吗？”

yingyinNormal.en: I've been published in peer-reviewed journals, I received a dissertation of the year award for experimental particle physics.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我在同行评审刊物里发表过论文，我在实验粒子物理学方面获得过年度专题论文奖。

yingyinNormal.en: Lord Moran, he's a Peer of the Realm. Normally he'd sit in the House. Tonight, there's an all-night sitting to vote on the new anti-terrorism bill.
yingyinNormal.zh: 莫兰爵士，世袭贵族，他应该在上议院里，今晚大家会在一起为反恐法案投票。

yingyinNormal.en: Got it. All right, I'm thinking one way to counter bias in the peer-review process, is for papers to be submitted under gender-neutral names. Like S. Smith instead of Samantha Smith.
yingyinNormal.zh: 明白，我想到了一个避免在同行评审阶段遭受歧视的方法，就是报告都用中性名字递交，比如S·史密斯，而不是沙曼莎·史密斯。

yingyinNormal.en: In the past few weeks, unburdened by trivial decisions, I've co-authored two papers in notable peer reviewed journals, and I'm close to figuring out why the Large Hadron Collider has yet to isolate the Higgs boson particle.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这几周，因为不用做琐碎的决定，我已经和别人合作在著名同行评审期刊上发表了两篇论文，我也就快搞清楚大型强子对撞机是如何分离出希格斯玻色子的。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2016.6-2023.6年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Less sport, and fewer meetings with <highlight>peers</highlight> correlated with lower wellbeing as did less time reading print media (newspapers) and, surprisingly, less time doing homework.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 体育活动的减少和与同龄人的较少的聚会会导致幸福感降低，阅读印刷媒体(报纸)的时间减少，令人惊讶的是，家庭作业的时间也会减少。

examination_example.sentence: As fifth-graders, children with early attention problems obtained grades at least 8% lower than those of their <highlight>peers</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 五年级时，有早期注意力障碍的儿童的成绩比同龄人低至少8%。

examination_example.sentence: By fifth grade, children with early attention difficulties had lower grades and reading achievement scores than their <highlight>peers</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 到五年级时，早期注意力集中困难的孩子的成绩和阅读成就分数都比同龄人低。

examination_example.sentence: Children not as liked by their first-grade <highlight>peers</highlight> had slightly lower grades in fifth grade, while those with higher social acceptance had higher grades.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 不被一年级同龄人喜欢的孩子，五年级的时候，成绩会略低，而社会认可度较高的孩子则成绩较高。

examination_example.sentence: Likability by <highlight>peers</highlight> also had a modest effect on academic performance.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 同伴的喜爱程度对学业成绩也有一定的影响。

examination_example.sentence: Social acceptance by <highlight>peers</highlight> in early childhood also predicted grades in fifth grade.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 幼儿期同伴的社会接受度也能预测五年级的成绩。

由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

精选2016-2023年8年间试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。
